text=!!Introduction%0a[[#excerpt]]%0a[[ {{LaTeX}} -> Technology.LaTeX ]] is a fabulous mark-up language for%0acreating all kinds of documents, from simple to complex, that is%0amostly intended for typeset works. (There are tools to convert%0a{{LaTeX}} to HTML, but if you are doing dual-deployment, it may be%0abetter to start off from a different, but common format that can be%0aconverted into either.)%0a[[#excerptend]]%0a%0a!!my-latex-mode%0a@@latex-mode@@ is invoked on a file by the%0a[[usual means -> EmacsModes]]%0aand has some pretty nice features. I like to use the @@pdflatex@@%0atoolchain for running {{LaTeX}} on my files, but this also presents a%0aproblem with the standard @@tex-view@@ and @@tex-print@@ functions, as%0athey ''hard-wire'' in the need for a @@.dvi@@ file. I wrote a file%0athat can be loaded whenever @@tex-mode@@ or @@latex-mode@@ is invoked%0avia the standard Emacs [[hooks -> EmacsUsingHooks]] mechanism.%0a%0aThe file creates a new set of customisable variables and functions%0ageared toward handling `PDFs instead of @@.dvi@@ files. The keyboard%0acommands normally associated with @@tex-view@@ and @@tex-print@@ are%0aremapped to these new functions.%0a%0a!!! New variables:%0a%0a:@@tex-pdf-print-command@@:Command used to print a pdf (default: "xpdf")%0a:@@tex-alt-pdf-print-command@@:An alternate command to print the pdf (default: "xpdf")%0a:@@tex-pdf-view-commant@@:Command used to view a pdf%0a** X Windows default: "xpdf"%0a** MS Windows default: "acroread"%0a** Non-specified: "open" ''(this is mostly used for OS/X.)''%0a%0a!!! New functions:%0a%0a:@@tex-pdf-print@@:Prints the pdf created%0a:@@tex-alt-pdf-print@@:Alternative method for printing the pdf%0a:@@tex-pdf-view@@:View the pdf%0a%0a!!! Obtaining my-latex-mode%0a%0a:Repository:https://gitorious.org/latex-stuff/my-latex-mode%0a%0aClone the repository into a temporary directory, then move%0a@@my-latex-mode.el@@ to a directory on your @@emacs@@ @@load-path@@.%0a%0a!!! Installing my-latex-mode%0a%0aModify your @@.emacs@@ file with the following:%0a%0a(:source lang=lisp:)%0a(add-hook 'latex-mode-hook (require 'my-latex-mode))%0a(:sourceend:)%0a%0aThen, whenever you load a latex file, these functions will also be%0aavailable. The file remaps the [@C-c C-v@] and [@C-c C-p@] keys to use%0athe new pdf functions.%0a%0a>>comment%3c%3c%0aMetadata stays at end%0a%0aSummary:a mode for editing {{LaTeX}} files%0aParent:(Technology.)Emacs%0aIncludeMe:[[Technology.Emacs]]%0aCategories:[[!Articles]]%0aTags: emacs, latex, editing, word processing%0a(:tags-hide  emacs, latex, editing, word processing:)%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a%0a
