diff:1331764512:1331764512:=1,68d0%0a%3c (:if false:)%0a%3c Summary:a mode for editing {$LaTeX} files%0a%3c Parent:Technology(.Emacs)%0a%3c IncludeMe:[[Technology.Emacs]]%0a%3c Categories:[[!Articles]]%0a%3c Tags: emacs, latex, editing, word processing%0a%3c (:tags-hide  emacs, latex, editing, word processing:)%0a%3c (:ifend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!Introduction%0a%3c [[ {$LaTeX} -> Technology.LaTeX ]] is a fabulous mark-up language for%0a%3c creating all kinds of documents, from simple to complex, that is%0a%3c mostly intended for typeset works. (There are tools to convert%0a%3c {$LaTeX} to HTML, but if you are doing dual-deployment, it may be%0a%3c better to start off from a different, but common format that can be%0a%3c converted into either.)%0a%3c %0a%3c !!my-latex-mode%0a%3c @@latex-mode@@ is invoked on a file by the%0a%3c [[usual means -> EmacsModes]]%0a%3c and has some pretty nice features. I like to use the @@pdflatex@@%0a%3c toolchain for running {$LaTeX} on my files, but this also presents a%0a%3c problem with the standard @@tex-view@@ and @@tex-print@@ functions, as%0a%3c they ''hard-wire'' in the need for a @@.dvi@@ file. I wrote a file%0a%3c that can be loaded whenever @@tex-mode@@ or @@latex-mode@@ is invoked%0a%3c via the standard Emacs [[hooks -> EmacsUsingHooks]] mechanism.%0a%3c %0a%3c The file creates a new set of customisable variables and functions%0a%3c geared toward handling `PDFs instead of @@.dvi@@ files. The keyboard%0a%3c commands normally associated with @@tex-view@@ and @@tex-print@@ are%0a%3c remapped to these new functions.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! New variables:%0a%3c %0a%3c :@@tex-pdf-print-command@@:Command used to print a pdf (default:%0a%3c "xpdf")%0a%3c :@@tex-alt-pdf-print-command@@:An alternate command to print the pdf%0a%3c (default: "xpdf")%0a%3c :@@tex-pdf-view-commant@@:Command used to view a pdf%0a%3c ** X Windows default: "xpdf"%0a%3c ** MS Windows default: "acroread"%0a%3c ** Non-specified: "open" ''(this is mostly used for OS/X.)''%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! New functions:%0a%3c %0a%3c :@@tex-pdf-print@@:Prints the pdf created%0a%3c :@@tex-alt-pdf-print@@:Alternative method for printing the pdf%0a%3c :@@tex-pdf-view@@:View the pdf%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! Obtaining my-latex-mode%0a%3c %0a%3c :Repository:https://gitorious.org/latex-stuff/my-latex-mode%0a%3c %0a%3c Clone the repository into a temporary directory, then move%0a%3c @@my-latex-mode.el@@ to a directory on your @@emacs@@ @@load-path@@.%0a%3c %0a%3c !!! Installing my-latex-mode%0a%3c %0a%3c Modify your @@.emacs@@ file with the following:%0a%3c %0a%3c (:source lang=lisp:)%0a%3c (add-hook 'latex-mode-hook (require 'my-latex-mode))%0a%3c (:sourceend:)%0a%3c %0a%3c Then, whenever you load a latex file, these functions will also be%0a%3c available. The file remaps the [@C-c C-v@] and [@C-c C-p@] keys to use%0a%3c the new pdf functions.%0a%3c %0a
